post_text:
Good morning EUSD families. Our superintendent, Dr. Lightle, presented the Learning Continuity and Attendance Plan to the District Advisory Committee and the District English Learner Advisory Committee to elicit input. He addressed questions that arose during the meetings, and has responded to all of the questions in the attached document. The final draft of the plan will be reviewed by the EUSD Board of Trustees at the September 16 board meeting and further input regarding the plan may be submitted during the public hearing. The final plan will be submitted to the board for approval on September 23. For further information on the Learning Continuity and Attendance Plan, please contact Dr. Donna Smith by email (dsmith@eastsideusd.org) or phone (661.952.1200).

You can view the Superintendent's Written Response on our district homepage under "Latest News": https://www.eastsideusd.org/

shared_text:
Columbia Elementary School
August 23 at 11:54 PM ·

Good evening Columbia families. First off we want to thank you for your patience and working with us as we started the new school year. We have some information for the upcoming week. This Wednesday, August 26th will be our Virtual Back to School Night. You will be able to participate in Back to School Night through your child’s Google classroom. We will be running two sessions, for 30 minutes each session. Session 1 will meet from 5:00pm – 5:30 pm and Session 2 will be from 5:40pm – 6:10pm. During these sessions, you will get information from your child’s teacher about class structure and expectations. General classroom questions can be answered during these sessions. If you have specific questions about your child, you can make an appointment with the teacher. Also, we need everyone to turn in their first day packets. They are a group of forms that were handed out when you picked up your child’s chromebook or tablet. If you do not have them, please stop by the front office to get one.

Free Wi-Fi from Spectrum! Charter and Comcast announced Friday that they would offer 60 days of complimentary broadband to homes with K-12 or college students. For households that do not already have a subscription, Charter said that beginning Monday, it will provide free Spectrum broadband and Wi-Fi up to 100 Mbps, and that installation fees will be waived.
To enroll for Charter's service, call 844-488-8395; for Comcast's, 855-846-8376 for English speakers or 855-765-6995 for Spanish speakers, or go to www.internetessentials.com.

post_text:
Eastside Union School District is developing our Local Control and Accountability Plan (LCAP) for the 2020 – 2021 through the 2022-2023 school years. Your input and suggestions would be greatly appreciated.

We will align the actions in our plan with the Board of Trustee goals.This week, we are focusing on Goal 2: Promote a safe and caring learning environment.

Please join the conversation, by commenting on any of the questions below between February 14 – February 21, 2020:

What would make our school the best school ever?
How does PBIS / Olweus Bully Prevention help keep the school safe?
What can we do to build upon positive relationships (student – teacher / student-student)?

Thank you for your ongoing support of Eastside Union School District!

post_text:
El Distrito Escolar de la Unión de Eastside está desarrollando nuestro Plan del Control Local y Rendición de Cuentas (LCAP) para los años escolares 2020-2021 hasta el 2022-2023. Sus aportaciones y sugerencias serán muy agradecidas. Alinearemos las acciones de nuestro plan con las metas de la Mesa Directiva.

Esta semana nos centramos en el Objetivo 1: Mejorar el aprendizaje, el rendimiento y el éxito de los estudiantes.

Por favor, únase a la conversación, comentando sobre cualquiera de las siguientes preguntas entre el 7 y el 14 de febrero de 2020:
¿Qué le gusta a usted con respecto a la escuela de su hijo?
¿Qué pueden hacer los maestros y directores para ayudar a su hijo a aprender mejor? (Piense en programas, actividades y contenido).
¿Cómo podemos aprovechar mejor la tecnología como una herramienta de aprendizaje?

¡Gracias por su continuo apoyo al Distrito Escolar de la Unión de Eastside!
